FeedPackage.Description:
Manage SEPA (Single Euro Payments Area) Credit and Debit Transfer for SEPA or international order. Only one PaymentInformation is managed but it can manage multiple transactions.
The debitor is common to all transactions in a Credit transfer. The creditor is common to all transactions in a Debit transfer. It follows the "Customer Credit Transfer Initiation" <pain.001.001.03> defined in ISO 20022 - the original repository also includes some specific french rules (field used size != allowed size). Debit uses <pain.008.001.02> defined in ISO 20022 and the same french restrictions.
This version of the SepaWriter repository has automatic conversion to UPPERCASE for Bic/IBAN, with Regex added for Bic and IBAN code validation.
FeedPackage.Summary: Manage SEPA (Single Euro Payments Area) Credit and Debit Transfer for SEPA or international order. Only one PaymentInformation is managed but it can manage multiple transactions.

FeedPackage.Description:
Spark contains a number of very useful Sitecore utilities They include:
A Datasource Resolver that automatically escapes XPath statements for use by "query" and "fast"
A rule and event framework that allows programmers to explicitly specify required conditions for parameters that are typically not specified in the pipeline, such as database, site, and language.
Extensions to Language that make it easier to transition between ISO-codes, Language Items and Globalization.Language objects.
A handful of Rules for automatically moving Items to appropriate subfolders to create blog-like URLs.
FeedPackage.Summary: A Sitecore extension library used by the Spark namespace.
FeedPackage.Title: Spark.Sitecore

FeedPackage.Description:
All of these fields have been tested against Sitecore 6.6.x. Most should work with Sitecore 7.x Fields Included:
Filtered Tree, Queryable Treelist, Site-Based Droptree, Site-Based Image, Site-Based Multilist, Site-Based Treelist, Tokenized List
Thank you to Ed Lane for his help in porting some of these to Sitecore 6.6 and for his work on Tokenized List.
FeedPackage.Summary: A collection of aftermarket fields for the Sitecore content editor
FeedPackage.Title: Spark.Sitecore.Client

FeedPackage.Description:
This library supports a number of regularly-requested SEO features, implemented in Sitecore. Some of these have been implemented elsewhere, but I believe my approach is stronger for multi-site, multi-language installations.
Features Included: Multi-site 404 page subsystem that returns an actual 404 response code. Automatic Robots.txt support - configurable for each Sitecore server in your installation. Automatic Sitemap.xml support - fully multi-site capable; can be configured to support a wide array of information architectures. Rule-based approach to ensuring that Sitecore Items get the most url-friendly name possible.
FeedPackage.Summary: A number of SEO-specific modules for Sitecore.
FeedPackage.Title: Spark.Sitecore.Seo

FeedPackage.Description:
This library contains the following useful classes:
Querystring Helper: Allows for easy appending, concatenating, and manipulating Querystrings.
UrlHelper: Manages Querystring parameters through the URL objects.
Pagination: Headless logic for producing web pages that support paginated result sets.
